{"id":933,"date":"2024-09-09T16:31:50","date_gmt":"2024-09-09T16:31:50","guid":{"rendered":"http:\/\/localhost\/tlrfmdu\/?p=933"},"modified":"2024-09-09T16:31:52","modified_gmt":"2024-09-09T16:31:52","slug":"new-village-units-join-unorganized-labour-unions-of-tlrf","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"http:\/\/localhost\/tlrfmdu\/index.php\/new-village-units-join-unorganized-labour-unions-of-tlrf\/","title":{"rendered":"New village units join unorganized labour unions of TLRF"},"content":{"rendered":"\n<p>Tamilnadu Labourers\u2019 Rights Federation (TLRF) got strengthened with new units joining the federations with number of unorganized workers registering as members. In the month of August 2024, more than 50 women workers from Vilacheri, Kalappanpatti, and Kamaatchipuram&nbsp; of Madurai district, Ondipulinaayakanur of Virudhunagar district and Irulakkudumbanpatti of Dindigul district became members of registered unions by paying Rs 120 as annual subscription. Some of the members also registered themselves with the unorganized workers\u2019 welfare board.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Union officials earlier hand contact meetings with these workers at their villages explaining the nature and function of the unions and the federation. After carefully considering the activities and the purpose of these unions, new members agreed to be members of these unions.&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Public events were held in the villages to show the formal inclusion of the village units into the federation. Officials of the federation and the unions participated in the events explaining publicly the objectives of the federation. In some events there were cultural events to make it a celebration.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-gallery has-nested-images columns-default is-cropped wp-block-gallery-1 is-layout-flex wp-block-gallery-is-layout-flex\">\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img fetchpriority=\"high\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"1024\" height=\"472\" data-id=\"794\" src=\"htt